I've sanity checked/tested 0.17.1rc1 on openBSD 6.4. Compiling (with wallet, no-gui), running the unit/functional tests, running the binary and syncing for a while.

I've posted a `Vagrantfile` which "wraps up" the vm configuration, installing dependencies etc [here](https://github.com/fanquake/core-review/tree/master/vagrant) if anyone is interested. It's a fairly easy way to get a test environment setup quickly. I'll add more box definitions while testing rc1.

@Sjors I've updated your comment to include the link to the rc1 binaries.
